# Session Workflow

## Start Of Every New Chat

1. Read `docs/CURSOR_2.0_RULES_FINAL.md` with the read-file tool.
2. Summarize 3-5 key rules and state: `✅ Rules reading completed - I have read docs/CURSOR_2.0_RULES_FINAL.md and will follow all rules`.
3. Read `docs/AGENT_HANDOVER.md` and the 2-3 most recent `docs/session_logs/*.md`.
4. Read `docs/CHANGELOG.md` for recent changes.
5. Run `git status --short --branch` before pull, edits, commits, or pushes.
6. Run `git log --oneline -10` to understand recent work.

Do not start substantive work before the rules confirmation is done.

## During Work

- Preserve user changes. Never revert or overwrite unrelated work.
- Ask before destructive actions or production writes.
- Keep changes scoped to the request; document important risks.

## End Of Completed Work

- Create a session log from `docs/session_logs/TEMPLATE.md`.
- Update `docs/AGENT_HANDOVER.md` and relevant docs.
- Validate changed files with targeted tests/lints where practical.
- Commit and push only when allowed by the active agent/git instructions and user request.
